Question time!  When bandcamp started out, we began by tracking all tasks and bugs along side the detailed specs from design on our local install of MediaWiki. Now that we’re more than a couple of developers, it’s becoming a huge pain in the ass to manage bugs on a wiki.  What do you all use for bug tracking?
Most places I've worked use Jira.
From my point of view (developer) I love trello. From my project manager point of view, he prefers JIRA
but for my own use i use Trello and asana
what do you like about Jira?
I'm not a huge fan of Jira but I guess I only "like" it because I'm familiar with it from all my previous jobs. Some Jira setups are overly complex.
is there anything you _wish_ you used instead of jira?
Wish I just used Github issues + projects but that doesn't work for PM and QA. My workflow is 99% in Android Studio and Github.
My personal stuff, I used to use Asana but now moved to Github/Gitlab issues + project/board.
we might move to github issues + projects
I wonder if there is a standalone version of something like github issues… we don’t use github, but I do like the simplicity of GH issues

attachments.title: How to publish artifacts signatures (.asc files) using maven-publish plugin?
attachments.text: It's not yet possible to upload artifact signatures via the new maven-publish plugin. The problem is that there's no way to tell Gradle that the '.asc' file is not a regular artifact but is in fact auxiliary to the main artifact. This is on the development roadmap for publishing support, but is not currently on our priority list.
